A class is a blueprint or template used to create objects
SYNTAX----------->
 class ClassName:
     pass

A class contain 
  *Constructor 
  *Attribute
  *Methodes

***constuctor(__init__method)***
1.A constructor is a special method that runs automatically when an object is created
2.It is used to initialize (set) the instance attributes of the object
SYNTAX--------------->
def __init__(self, parameters):
    initialize attributes

***Attribute***
Two types:
01.Class Attributes → same for all objects
02.Instance Attributes → different for each object


***Methodes***
Methods are functions inside a class that perform actions
Example types:
  *Instance methods
  *Class methods
  *Static methods
